  <data key="d1">"St Elizabeths Hospital is a psychiatric hospital in Washington, D.C., where Ezra Pound was confined between 1945 and 1958. It opened in 1855 as the first federally operated psychiatric hospital in the United States and was designated a National Historic Landmark in 1990."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e3843ca9496d241998ffa77892e9572</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VISITS TO ST ELIZABETHS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Visits to St Elizabeths is a poem by Elizabeth Bishop that models the English nursery rhyme 'This is the house that Jack built'. The poem describes the experience of visiting St Elizabeths Hospital and the confinement of Ezra Pound there."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e3843ca9496d241998ffa77892e9572</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
